text:
1111 Park Avenue, at S. E. corner of 90th Street, a new apartment building, nearing completion, replacing four 5-story houses on Park Avenue and Nos. 104-10 East 90th Street. The building immediately below it is only two or three years older.

1925.

Joseph Smith, Photographer.

1112 Park Avenue, on S.W. corner of 90th Street, newly completed, replacing two 5-story buildings. In 1930 the 7-story double apartment house (Meteor) on the N.W. corner of 89th Street will be replaced by a 17-story building, but the two little houses in between will stay. 1927.

Knickerbocker Photo Service.
Park Avenue, west side, between 91st and 90th Streets, showing 1130 on 91st Street corner, erected about 1926. About 1927.
